The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Delhi take a huge lead
                                                                                                                                                                                                     Delhi take a huge lead
                      
	New Delhi: Teenaged Delhi batsman Virat Kohli and seasoned opener Aakash Chopra missed double hundreds but steered Delhi to a mammoth 516 for four against Pakistanis Sui Northern Gas Pipeline Limited (SNGPL) on the rain-curtailed third and penultimate day of the Mohammad Nissar Trophy cricket match here on Wednesday.         
	Kohli fell just three runs short while Chopra smashed 182, contributing 385 runs in a partnership that lasted 536 balls.         
	Rajat Bhatia was batting on 32 and Mayank Tehlan was on 24 when rains played spoilsport an hour and 20 minutes before scheduled close of play. Seventeen overs of the days play were lost.         
	Kohli and Chopra put Delhi in an advantageous position with a huge lead of 384 runs on another frustrating day for the bowlers.         
